          option[selected="selected" data-img-src="img/rena.png"]
            | Rena Cugelman
          option[data-img-src="img/tavis.png"]
            | Tavis Lochhead
          option[data-img-src="img/brian.png"]
            | Brain Cugelman
      p
        | Use 
        code.highlighter-rouge
          | data-img-src
        |  attribute to attache images.
      h2.ui.header.title-m
        | Custom Style / Markup
      p
        i
          | Image Select
        |  allows the customization of THML markup and styles it uses to insert images. For example, to style the image directly, add your own css classes, or define your own HTML markup which would include the image and text placement.
      p
        | The following example adds a black border to the images and places the text before the image (similar to 
        strong
          | rtl
        |  mode).
      select.my-select-border[multiple="multiple"]
        option[data-img-src="img/adnan.png"]
          | Adnan Sagar
        option[data-img-src="img/rena.png"]
          | Rena Cugelman
        option[selected="selected" data-img-src="img/tavis.png"]
          | Tavis Lochhead
        option[selected="selected" data-img-src="img/brian.png"]
          | Brain Cugelman
      br
      br
      p
        | It simply adds the required css styles directly to the image template
      code.javascript.cm-s-mdn-like
        | $(".my-select").chosen({ width:"100%", html_template: '{text} <img style="border:3px solid #ff703d;padding:0px;margin-right:4px" class="{class_name}" src="{url}" />' });
      p
        | Use the 
        code.highlighter-rouge
          | html_template
        |  to write your own markup. Make sure you always include the two place hodlers 
        code.highlighter-rouge
          | {class_name}
        |  and 
        code.highlighter-rouge
          | {url}
        | , which are being used internally to insert the approperiate class name, and image url for each options element
      h2.ui.header.title-m
